synthesis_analysis: The AI excels at validating feelings and providing practical, structured steps, which builds trust and enables action. Its primary weakness is addressing emotional and physiological anxiety reactively, often missing opportunities to integrate calming techniques or probe root causes. To improve, it must proactively pair conversational strategies with simple anxiety-management tools and gently explore underlying fears. The highest priority is evolving beyond reactive advice to holistically address confidence and real-time emotional regulation.
